On the other hand, the median represents the middle value when the data is arranged in ascending or descending order. It is useful when the data has outliers or extreme values that could significantly affect the arithmetic mean.

The mode represents the value that occurs most frequently in a dataset. It is useful when dealing with categorical or discrete data.

